# GitHub sync (required)

After completing meaningful code or content changes in this project, **always** commit and push to GitHub without waiting for the user to ask.

## Account

- GitHub username: `tbs4one`
- Commit author email: `tbs4one@live.com`
- Commit author name: `tbs4one`
- Remote repo: `https://github.com/tbs4one/olas-general-merchant.git` (`origin`)

## How to commit (do not change git config)

Never run `git config`. For every commit, set identity only for that command:

```bash
git -c user.name="tbs4one" -c user.email="tbs4one@live.com" commit -m "message"
```

## Sync steps

1. `git status` / `git diff` / recent `git log` (parallel)
2. Stage relevant files (`git add`); do not commit secrets (`.env`, credentials)
3. Commit with a clear message (why over what)
4. `git push -u origin HEAD` (or `git push` if tracking exists)
5. If push fails because remote is ahead, pull/rebase only if safe; otherwise tell the user

## Scope

- Sync after features, fixes, design updates, and asset changes
- Skip empty commits when there is nothing to sync
- Prefer one sync at the end of a task rather than many tiny pushes mid-task
